# Documentation language (CalacaCMS monorepo)

## English (required)

All **project documentation** under these paths must be **English**:

- `cms/` — including `cms/docs/`, README files, knowledge-base style Markdown, and agent-facing instructions in this tree
- `docs/` — Starlight documentation site (`src/content/docs/`, etc.)
- `agent-context/` — knowledge base and SSOT for humans and AI agents (`PROJECT_SSOT.md`, research, plans)
- `landing/` — README, Astro pages, and **all user-facing marketing copy** (headlines, CTAs, body text)

When you **create or edit** Markdown, README, Astro/markup copy, or similar material in those directories, write in clear **English** — including marketing and product messaging on the landing site.

## Dutch (allowed)

At the **workspace root** only, Markdown such as `ROADMAP.md`, `cms-wensen.md`, and narrative sections in root `AGENTS.md` **may be Dutch** (moedertaal van de maintainer).

## Unchanged

- **Code comments**, **identifiers**, and **commit messages**: **English** everywhere (see `cms/AGENTS.md`).
- Explanations in chat: follow user language when the user writes in Dutch (`cms/AGENTS.md` — Learned User Preferences).
